
The *Taskbar* consists of
  • → Windows/configuration/Start-menu
  • Taskbar buttons
  • Toolbars (optional)
  • → Windows/Appearance/Taskbar/notification-area[Notification area]
  • Quick launch bar (Windows Vista and earlier only)
  • News and Interests, an extremly distracting rectangle that tells me if its sunny or raining (which I can also see when looking out of my *real* window).

The → Windows/keyboard-shortcuts[keyboard shortcut] `win+t` cycles through the apps on the taskbar.

*News and Interests* can be removed (hidden) from the Taskbar by setting the registry value `ShellFeedsTaskbarViewMode` to 2 under the registry key
→ Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Windows/CurrentVersion/Feeds[`HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Feeds`].

sa:

  → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/winUserLanguageList

  → Windows/Appearance/Taskbar/Language-Bar[Language bar]

  → Windows/dirs/Users/username/AppData/Roaming/Microsoft/Internet-Explorer/Quick-Launch/User-Pinned/TaskBar[`%APPDATA%\Microsoft\Internet Explorer\Quick Launch\User Pinned\TaskBar`]

  → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/DevModeRunAsUserConfig_msc[`DevModeRunAsUserConfig.msc`]
